# Font Sizing Consistency

Within a given UI region (a section, card, or row), **do not vary font size to signal
importance**. Keep text at one consistent size and instead differentiate using:

- **weight** (`font-normal` → `font-medium` → `font-semibold` → `font-bold`)
- **color** (e.g. `text-neutral-400` for muted, `text-neutral-900` for primary, `text-primary-600` for brand emphasis)

The default body size is `text-sm`. Large display type (page hero `h1`, `.section-title`)
is the deliberate exception and may scale with `clamp()`.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — three different sizes to show hierarchy
<p className="text-base font-semibold">Dennis Lim</p>
<p className="text-xs text-neutral-400">R055990G</p>
<p className="text-sm text-neutral-600">{bio}</p>

// ✅ GOOD — one size, hierarchy via weight + color
<p className="text-sm font-bold text-neutral-900">Dennis Lim</p>
<p className="text-sm font-normal text-neutral-400">R055990G</p>
<p className="text-sm font-normal text-neutral-600">{bio}</p>
```

Avoid mixing `font-mono` into content rows that otherwise use the body font — it changes
the visual size/rhythm even at the same nominal size.
